 a function is a reusable block of code that performs a specific task or set of tasks.
 Functions allow you to write logic, group related code, and make your code more organized and maintainable.
 A JavaScript function is defined with the function keyword, followed by a name, followed by parentheses ().
 he code to be executed, by the function, is placed inside curly brackets: {}
 Function Expressions variable  used as an argument to other functions.
 A function expression in JavaScript is a way to define a function as part of an expression.


 Synchronous Execution 
 tasks are executed sequentially, one after another, in the order they appear in the code. Each task must complete before the next one starts.

 Asynchronous Execution
 tasks are executed concurrently, and the program doesn't wait for a task to finish before moving on to the next one. Asynchronous operations are typically used for tasks that may take some time to complete
